Class ClinicManagerController

java.lang.Object
clinic.cs213project3.ClinicManagerController
public class ClinicManagerController extends Object
The controller class for managing events in the JavaFX UI.
Author:
Aarush Desai, Rohan Vuppunuthula

  • Method Details

    • scheduleAppointment

      private void scheduleAppointment()
      Method schedules a new appointment in the clinic manager. Event is triggered upon pressing "Schedule Appointment" button.

    • cancelAppointment

      private void cancelAppointment()
      Method cancels an existing appointment in the clinic manager. Event is triggered upon pressing "Cancel Appointment" button.

    • rescheduleAppointment

      private void rescheduleAppointment()
      Method reschedules an existing appointment in the clinic manager. Event is triggered upon pressing "Reschedule Appointment" button.

    • displayFunds

      private void displayFunds()
      Method displays dispersed funds for patients and providers. User can choose to display patient bills or provider credits.

    • displayAppointments

      private void displayAppointments()
      Method displays existing appointments in a specified sorting order. User can choose to sort all appointments by date, patient, or location. User can choose to display only office or imaging appointments sorted by location.

    • createBackendVariables

      private void createBackendVariables()
      Helper method initializes all the backend instance variables.

    • fillChoiceBoxes

      private void fillChoiceBoxes()
      Helper method fills data into all choice boxes in the UI.

    • createProviderButtonListener

      private void createProviderButtonListener()
      Helper method creates a listener for the radio buttons in the "Schedule" tab. Either only an office or imaging appointment can be chosen, not both.

    • createSortingListener

      private void createSortingListener()
      Helper method creates a listener for the radio buttons in the "Appointments" tab. If all appointments are chosen, you can choose to sort them by date, patient, or location. If only office or imaging appointments are chosen, you cannot choose the sorting order.

    • clearEventLog

      private void clearEventLog()
      Method clears the event logger/text area in the UI.

    • checkForDateInput

      private String checkForDateInput(javafx.scene.control.DatePicker dateBox)
      Helper method extracts date from a given date picker. Date is formatted with the month, day, and year separated by "/" character.
      Parameters:
      dateBox - The date picker.
      Returns:
      The date as string, or null if the date picker is empty.

    • gatherProviderInput

      private String gatherProviderInput(String commandLetter, String fullCommand)
      Helper method collects input from the doctor/imaging radio buttons. Method is used to construct the command for scheduling an appointment.
      Parameters:
      commandLetter - The letter of the command.
      fullCommand - The command string to complete.
      Returns:
      The full command with the appropriate token added at the end, else null of radio buttons are empty.

    • displayTableOfProviders

      private void displayTableOfProviders()
      Method displays the providers to the UI table view under the "Providers" tab. The table shows the providers' name, type, location, specialty, and rate.

    • parseDate

      private Date parseDate(String dateStr)
      Helper method parses a date string and returns a Date object.
      Parameters:
      dateStr - The date in "MM/DD/YYYY" format.
      Returns:
      The Date object or null if string is invalid.

    • parseTimeslot

      private Timeslot parseTimeslot(String timeslotStr)
      Parses a timeslot string and returns a Timeslot object.
      Parameters:
      timeslotStr - The timeslot number as a string.
      Returns:
      The Timeslot object or null if string is invalid.

    • parseRadiology

      private Radiology parseRadiology(String roomStr)
      Parses a room string and returns a Radiology object.
      Parameters:
      roomStr - The imaging room as a string.
      Returns:
      The Radiology object or null if string is invalid.

    • parseDoctor

      private Doctor parseDoctor(String npi)
      Finds the doctor associated with a given npi identification.
      Parameters:
      npi - The doctor's npi.
      Returns:
      The Doctor object with the npi or null if npi does not exist.

    • findProvider

      private Person findProvider(Appointment apt)
      Finds the provider associated with an appointment in the list. First checks if appointment exists, then if provider is a doctor, and then returns the provider.
      Parameters:
      apt - The appointment we are searching for.
      Returns:
      The appointment's provider as a Person object, else null if appointment does not exist.

    • isProviderAvailable

      private boolean isProviderAvailable(Appointment apt)
      Checks if an appointment can be scheduled based on availability of its provider. Checks the whole list for an appointment with same provider, timeslot, and date.
      Parameters:
      apt - The appointment we want to schedule.
      Returns:
      True if no appointment in list has same provider, timeslot, and date, else False.

    • appendMedicalRecords

      private void appendMedicalRecords()
      All patients associated with appointments in the list are added to the medical record. Method only runs when PS command is entered.

    • isDateAndTimeValid

      private boolean isDateAndTimeValid(Date date, String dateStr, Timeslot timeslot, String timeslotStr)
      Helper method checks if date and timeslot can be used to schedule a new appointment. Method checks if the date is valid, comes after today, is weekday, and within six months of today. Method checks if timeslot is valid by checking if it exists.
      Parameters:
      date - The date object.
      dateStr - The date as a string.
      timeslot - The timeslot object.
      timeslotStr - The timeslot as a string.
      Returns:
      True if the date and timeslot can be used, else False.

    • isBirthdayValid

      private boolean isBirthdayValid(Date dob, String dobStr)
      Helper method checks if a date of birth for a patient is valid. Method checks if the date object is valid, and is a date before today.
      Parameters:
      dob - The date of birth as a date object.
      dobStr - The date of birth as a string.
      Returns:
      True if the date of birth is logically valid, else False.

    • canAppointmentBeScheduled

      private boolean canAppointmentBeScheduled(Appointment apt, Profile profile)
      Helper method checks if the appointment a patient wants to schedule exists in the list.
      Parameters:
      apt - The patient's appointment.
      profile - The patient's profile.
      Returns:
      True if the patient's appointment does not exist in list, else False.

    • isDoctorValid

      private boolean isDoctorValid(Appointment apt, Doctor doctor, String npi, String timeslotStr)
      Helper method checks if a doctor exists and is available to attend an appointment.
      Parameters:
      apt - The appointment we are checking the doctor is available for.
      doctor - The doctor of interest.
      npi - The doctor's unique npi.
      timeslotStr - The appointment's timeslot as a string.
      Returns:
      True if doctor exists and is available at the appointment's timeslot, else False.

    • readInProviders

      private void readInProviders(File file)
      Reads from a file in a list of providers and appends them to the clinic list. The list of providers includes both doctors and technicians. Any technicians are also appended to the front of the circular linked list.
      Parameters:
      file - The file object to read from.

    • addDoctors

      private void addDoctors(StringTokenizer tokens)
      Helper method appends a doctor to the list of providers.
      Parameters:
      tokens - The tokenizer used to append doctor.

    • addTechnicians

      private void addTechnicians(StringTokenizer tokens)
      Helper method appends a technician to the list of providers. Method also appends technician to the circular linked list.
      Parameters:
      tokens - The tokenizer used to append technician.

    • computeProviderCredit

      private int computeProviderCredit(Provider provider)
      Helper method computes the total credit earned by a single given provider. The provider can be either a doctor or a technician.
      Parameters:
      provider - The provider we compute the credit for.
      Returns:
      The total credit earned by the provider as an integer.

    • dCommand

      private void dCommand(StringTokenizer tokenizer)
      Schedules a new appointment with a doctor to the clinic's list.
      Parameters:
      tokenizer - The command line data tokens.

    • tCommand

      private void tCommand(StringTokenizer tokenizer)
      Schedules a new appointment with a technician to the clinic's list.
      Parameters:
      tokenizer - The command line data tokens.

    • cCommand

      private void cCommand(StringTokenizer tokenizer)
      Cancels/deletes an existing appointment from the clinic's list.
      Parameters:
      tokenizer - The command line data tokens.

    • rCommand

      private void rCommand(StringTokenizer tokenizer)
      Reschedules an existing doctor's appointment on the clinic's list. Clinic does not allow imaging appointments to be rescheduled.
      Parameters:
      tokenizer - The command line data tokens.

    • paCommand

      private void paCommand()
      Displays all existing appointments sorted by date, time, and provider's name.

    • ppCommand

      private void ppCommand()
      Displays all existing appointments sorted by the patient's profile, date, and timeslots.

    • plCommand

      private void plCommand()
      Displays all existing appointments sorted by county, date, and timeslot.

    • poCommand

      private void poCommand()
      Displays all existing office appointments sorted by county, date, and timeslot.

    • piCommand

      private void piCommand()
      Displays all existing radiology appointments sorted by county, date, and timeslot.

    • psCommand

      private void psCommand()
      Displays the billing information for all patients in the medical record. Computes bill based on number of completed visits for the patient. Method clears out the appointment list once bills are computed and displayed.

    • pcCommand

      private void pcCommand()
      Displays the credit information for all providers of the clinic. Computes credit based on the provider's set of completed visits with patients. Method does not clear out the appointment list once credits are computed.
